Agentic RAG Pipeline — Intelligent Document Q&A System

An intelligent document Q&A system that combines Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) with an Agentic Controller that dynamically decides whether to search documents or answer directly — built entirely with free, open-source tools.


 What Is This Project?
Most AI Q&A systems blindly send every question to an LLM and hope for the best. This project is different.
Agentic RAG Pipeline uses an intelligent Agent Controller that reads the user's question, decides the best strategy to answer it, and either:

Searches your PDF documents for context-specific questions
Answers directly from LLM knowledge for general questions

This means smarter, more accurate answers — and no wasted computation searching documents when it isn't needed.

How It Works — Step by Step
User Query
    ↓
Agent Controller (Decision Maker)
    ↓               ↓
SEARCH mode     DIRECT mode
    ↓               ↓
Load PDFs       Skip retrieval
    ↓               ↓
Chunk text      Send query
    ↓           directly to LLM
Embed chunks        ↓
    ↓           Generate answer
FAISS Vector Store
    ↓
Retrieve top-3
relevant chunks
    ↓
Build context prompt
    ↓
DistilGPT2 LLM
    ↓
Final Answer

Key Features

Agentic Decision Making — Agent Controller dynamically routes queries based on intent
PDF Document Ingestion — Loads and processes multiple PDFs from a folder automatically
Intelligent Chunking — Splits documents into 500-token chunks with 80-token overlap for optimal retrieval
Semantic Search — HuggingFace all-MiniLM-L6-v2 embeddings find meaning, not just keywords
FAISS Vector Store — Fast and efficient similarity search across document chunks
Local LLM — DistilGPT2 runs completely offline — no API keys, no cost, no internet needed
Zero Cost — Every tool used is completely free and open source


