⚙️ Installation
Step 1 — Clone the Repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/agentic-rag-pipeline.git
cd agentic-rag-pipeline
Step 2 — Create Virtual Environment
bashpython -m venv venv

# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

# Mac/Linux
source venv/bin/activate
Step 3 — Install Dependencies
bashpip install langchain langchain-community faiss-cpu transformers torch sentence-transformers pypdf
Step 4 — Add Your PDF Files
Create a data/ folder and add your PDF files:
bashmkdir data
# Copy your PDFs into the data/ folder
Step 5 — Run the Pipeline
bashpython rag_pipeline.py

🚀 How to Use
Add Your PDFs
Place any PDF files inside the data/ folder. The pipeline automatically loads all of them.
Query Types
Document Search Mode — triggered by keywords like: pdf, document, data, summarize, information, find
pythonquery = "Give me a 5-point summary from the PDF"
# Agent decides → SEARCH mode → retrieves document context → answers
Direct Answer Mode — triggered for general knowledge questions
pythonquery = "What is an Ideal Resume Format?"
# Agent decides → DIRECT mode → answers from LLM knowledge directly

🔍 Core Components Explained
1. Document Ingestion
pythondef load_docs(folder_path):
    docs = []
    for file in os.listdir(folder_path):
        if file.endswith(".pdf"):
            loader = PyPDFLoader(os.path.join(folder_path, file))
            docs.extend(loader.load())
    return docs
Automatically discovers and loads all PDFs from the data folder.
2. Intelligent Chunking
pythontext_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(
    chunk_size=500,
    chunk_overlap=80
)
Splits documents into 500-token chunks with 80-token overlap — preserving context at chunk boundaries.
3. Semantic Embeddings + Vector Store
pythonembedding_model = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(model_name="all-MiniLM-L6-v2")
db = FAISS.from_texts(texts, embedding_model)
retriever = db.as_retriever(search_kwargs={"k": 3})
Converts text to 384-dimensional vectors for semantic similarity search — finds meaning, not just keywords.
4. Agent Controller (The Brain)
pythondef agent_controller(query):
    q = query.lower()
    if any(word in q for word in ["pdf", "document", "data", "summarize", "information", "find"]):
        return "search"
    return "direct"
The decision engine that makes the pipeline "agentic" — routing queries intelligently.
5. RAG Execution Loop
pythondef rag_answer(query):
    action = agent_controller(query)
    if action == "search":
        results = retriever.invoke(query)
        context = "\n".join([r.page_content for r in results])
        final_prompt = f"Use this context:\n{context}\n\nAnswer:\n{query}"
    else:
        final_prompt = query
    response = llm(final_prompt)[0]["generated_text"]
    return response
The complete pipeline — from query to answer in one function.

